IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Goodwill Specialty Services creates employment and job-training opportunities for people who have significant disabilities or other challenges to employment by providing contract work for businesses; federal, state, and local government; and other community partners.
IRS990.MissionDesc: Develop job skills and employment opportunities for people with disabilities and other vocational disadvantages, striving to increase the self-sufficiency of the corporations's program participants.
IRS990.Desc: FEDERAL CONTRACTS - Goodwill Specialty Services Inc (GSSI) provides employment opportunities through contracts with separate government entities of the Federal Government. These are set aside contracts for people with severe disabilities through the Javits-Wagner-O'Day act of 1971. GSSI is currently engaged in custodial, postal services, and grounds maintenance contracts through this program. Employees are paid through a management and administrative services contract with Goodwill Industries Inc. In 2015, GSSI was responsible for over 3,000,000 square feet of buildings for various janitorial contracts at Offutt Airforce Base, Stratcom, Zorinsky Federal building, and Denney Federal building in Lincoln. GSSI was also responsible for grounds maintenance at the VA hospital in Omaha, NE and Grand Island NE. GSSI also operates two postal contracts at Offutt Airforce Base serving over 1000 airmen and incoming personnel.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: OTHER CONTRACTS - GSSI's commercial services division provides job opportunities for individuals with barriers to employment. Current contracts include commercial bus cleaning for MAT bus in Omaha, pressure washing for MAT bus in Omaha, custodial services for private businesses, and grounds maintenance for residential and commercial customers. Individuals are provided full or part time employment depending on their personal preference. Training relative to a job requirement is provided to ensure personnel are given an opportunity to understand what is expected of them and to provide a path for professional growth.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Goodwill accounts for uncertainties in accounting for income tax assets and liabilities using the guidance included in Financial Accounting Standards Board (FASB ) accounting standards codification (ASC) Topic 740 Income Taxes. There are no uncertainties that are reflected in the financial statements.

Goodwill Specialty Services, Inc. does not have employees, but instead, leases them from a related organization, Goodwill Industries, Inc. Goodwill Industries, Inc. has a formal compensation policy and the Executive Committee serves as the Compensation Committee for the organization. Executive compensation is set annually and monitored by the local Goodwill Board of Trustees, which utilizes outside independent professional resources in determining appropriate salary levels. Goodwill participates in local, regional, and national executive compensation salary and benefit surveys. This survey data is utilized by the Board as a framework to ensure competitive compensation in order to retain high performing employees, including the CEO. In addition to survey results, compensation is based on agency performance as well as individual performance.
Goodwill Industries made payments in 2015 to a 457F plan for Frank McGree $37,500 and Pauli Bishop $6400.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 3
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GSSI has entered into a management and administrative services contract with Goodwill Industries, Inc. (GWI) in which GWI will be responsible for management of the operations of the company including but not limited to administrative and managerial support, accounting and financial planning, management of corporate funds, personnel services, vocational training and education, clerical support, and all other services and support required to operate the company efficiently and in accordance with all federal, state, and board stipulated laws, regulations, and procedures. In consideration of these services to be performed, the company agrees to pay a management fee equivalent to all excess revenue, after meeting operating expenses of the company.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Goodwill Specialty Services, Inc. has one member which shall be Goodwill Industries, Inc.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Form 990 is prepared internally based on the audited financial statements of the organization. Once completed, the draft of the 990 is submitted to an independent CPA firm for review and comments. After addressing the comments by the CPA firm, the 990 is sent to the board of trustees prior to filing for their review.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A signed conflict of interest statement is obtained from each officer, member of the board of trustees, and key employees of the organization at least annually. Each statement documents direct business relationships, family business relationships, and inter and intra family and business relationships. For any official action of the board or its committees, individuals with whom a conflict may be construed, are precluded from voting. The Conflict of Interest Statements are maintained in the corporate files.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Annual report is published each year which includes the audited financial statements for the organization. This report is mailed to all major donors, referral agencies, and other interested parties. The report is also available online on at www.goodwillomaha.org. Hard copies of the report, Goodwill's governing documents, and conflict of interest policy are available upon request.
